<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 09 at 7:24PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...An area of snow will impact portions of southeastern Madison,
southeastern Beaverhead and south central Gallatin Counties through
830 PM MDT...
At 720 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of snow moving
eastward along the Montana Idaho border moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Poor visibility and roadways becoming snow covered and
slippery.
Locations impacted include...
West Yellowstone, Lima, Monida, Lakeview, Snowline and Raynolds Pass.
This includes the following highways...
Interstate 15 between mile markers 1 and 35.
Highway 191 between mile markers 1 and 20.
Highway 287 between mile markers 1 and 20.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
